          "finding": "GFM table detection requires checking the line after the header row for a separator regex /^\\|?[\\s|:=-]*-+[\\s|:=-]*\\|?$/; without this, table lines fall through to the paragraph accumulator and render as raw text."
        },
        {
          "path": "app/src/components/MarkdownView.tsx",
          "finding": "The paragraph accumulator must use an isTableStart(j) guard rather than a bare includes('|') check; the latter breaks any paragraph containing a pipe character."
        },
        {
          "path": "app/src/components/MarkdownView.tsx",
          "finding": "Bold/italic nodes must recursively call parseInline on their content; without recursion, nested spans like **`word`** render the backticks literally inside the bold text."
        },
        {
          "path": "app/src/components/MarkdownView.tsx",
          "finding": "Fenced code block detection must use trimStart() on each line to handle indented fences; the paragraph accumulator guard must use the same trimmed check."
        },
        {
          "path": "app/src/components/MarkdownView.tsx",
          "finding": "Double-backtick spans (``code``) must be matched before single-backtick spans in the inline regex to avoid the leading backtick being consumed as a separate token."
        },
        {
          "path": "app/src/components/EventItem.tsx",
          "line": 71,
          "finding": "The splitHeader function was prepending '…' to the body text when the header was hard-cut at a word boundary; this caused visible ellipses in collapsed cards."
        },
        {
          "path": "src/indexer.ts",
          "finding": "Skipping already-indexed CheckpointMessages uses findUnique + conditional create rather than upsert with update:{} to avoid unintended overwrites on the unique uuid field."
        },
        {
          "path": "prisma/schema.prisma",
          "finding": "CheckpointSessionLink uses @@unique([checkpointId, sessionId]) and @@index([sessionId]) to enable efficient lookup of all checkpoints containing a given session ID."
        }
      ],
      "workflow": [
        "Use 'git worktree add /tmp/name branch-name' to access files on another branch without switching; always clean up with 'git worktree remove' afterward.",
        "Prisma schema edits fail if the file hasn't been read in the current context; always Read the schema before attempting an Edit.",
        "When a server uses a compiled dist/, any code changes require both 'npm run build' and a server restart before they take effect in the running API.",
        "Re-indexing after a schema change (to backfill new columns) is safe because new messages are skipped via findUnique; only upserted records (sessions, summaries, links) are updated."
      ]
    },
    "friction": [
      "Port 3000 EADDRINUSE on server restarts required 'lsof -ti :3000 | xargs kill -9' before relaunching.",
      "Expo was accidentally started on port 8081 (the default) instead of the project's configured port 19006.",
      "First attempt stored the checkpoint summary as a JSON blob on CheckpointSession; user rejected this and required a normalized CheckpointSummary relation table, requiring a schema re-design.",
      "Prisma Edit calls failed multiple times because the schema file was not re-read before editing after prior modifications, causing old_string mismatches.",
      "The server silently failed to stay up after one restart attempt; a foreground run was needed to capture stderr and confirm it was actually running.",
      "Markdown rendering required three separate fix iterations: (1) missing table support, (2) double-backtick and indented fence handling, (3) nested inline parsing inside bold/italic nodes."
    ],
    "open_items": [
      "The checkpoint polling loop in server.ts runs git reset --hard HEAD every 30 seconds; this assumes the worktree is always on the correct branch and HEAD is always updated by Entire CLI — no error handling for git failures or stale worktrees.",
      "InteractionOverview generation fires non-blockingly on Stop events but there is no retry or error logging if the AI call fails silently.",
      "The CheckpointDetail screen fetches all messages for a checkpoint in a single query with no pagination; large checkpoints (2400+ messages) may cause performance issues.",
